    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-15T09:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-15T09:35:00-05:00" n="312"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d312">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.91/102: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-15T18:00:00+03:25"
                            >January 15, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 16—3:22 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18 [<hi rend="italic">28?</hi>]. Today I interviewed Foreign Minister<note n="8"
                        xml:id="d312fn8">Mohammed Saed.</note> regarding Department’s telegram No.
                    23 dated January 13, 11 p.m. and he assured me his Government is “flattered by,
                    appreciative of and thoroughly agreeable to” proposal to raise our respective
                    Legations to Embassies. He stated he was immediately telegraphing this favorable
                    attitude to his Minister at Washington.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ford</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
